dasanDslMIB.name: dasanDslMIB
dasanDslMIB.description: The MIB module to describe SDSL product.

moduleNumber.name: moduleNumber
moduleNumber.description: The number of DSL modules (regardless of their current state) present on this system.

moduleTableLastChange.name: moduleTableLastChange
moduleTableLastChange.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time of the last creation or deletion of an entry in the moduleTable. If the number of entries has been unchanged since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

moduleTable.name: moduleTable
moduleTable.description: A list of module entries. The number of entries is given by the value of moduleNumber.

moduleEntry.name: moduleEntry
moduleEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular module.

moduleIndex.name: moduleIndex
moduleIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each module. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1. The value for each interface sub-layer must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

moduleDescr.name: moduleDescr
moduleDescr.description: A textual string containing information about the module. This string should include the name of the manufacturer, the product name and the version of the interface hardware/software.

moduleType.name: moduleType
moduleType.description: The type of module. This string defines the type of DSL module type. For instance, this can be SDSL, VDSL or SDSL.

modulePhysAddress.name: modulePhysAddress
modulePhysAddress.description: The module's address at its ethernet interface. For example, this object normally contains a MAC address.

moduleOperStatus.name: moduleOperStatus
moduleOperStatus.description: The current operational state of the module.

moduleUpTime.name: moduleUpTime
moduleUpTime.description: Elasped time since this module has been boot up.

moduleAvailableMemory.name: moduleAvailableMemory
moduleAvailableMemory.description: The amount of free memory in this module.

modulePortNumber.name: modulePortNumber
modulePortNumber.description: The number of ethernet ports and ethernet-like DSL ports (regardless of their current state) present on this module.

modulePortIndexBase.name: modulePortIndexBase
modulePortIndexBase.description: Port index base for this module. Port index range of this module is from modulePortIndexBase to (modulePortInexBase + modulePortNumber - 1).

moduleSpecific.name: moduleSpecific
moduleSpecific.description: A reference to MIB definitions specific to the particular media being used to realize the module. It is recommended that this value point to an instance of a MIB object in the media-specific MIB, i.e., that this object have the semantics associated with the InstancePointer textual convention defined in RFC 1903. In fact, it is recommended that the module- specific MIB specify what value moduleSpecific should/can take for values of moduleType. If no MIB definitions specific to the particular media are available, the value should be set to the OBJECT IDENTIFIER { 0 0 }.

dsDslPortNumber.name: dsDslPortNumber
dsDslPortNumber.description: The number of DSL modules (regardless of their current state) present on this system.

dsDslPortTable.name: dsDslPortTable
dsDslPortTable.description: A list of module entries. The number of entries is given by the value of moduleNumber.

dsDslPortEntry.name: dsDslPortEntry
dsDslPortEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular port.

portIndex.name: portIndex
portIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each module. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1. The value for each interface sub-layer must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

portDescr.name: portDescr
portDescr.description: A textual string containing information about the port.

portType.name: portType
portType.description: The type of communication port. This string defines the type of port. Each module has one or more ethernet port(s) and xDSL ports.

portIfIndex.name: portIfIndex
portIfIndex.description: ifIndex which is defined in interface mib.

portAdminStatus.name: portAdminStatus
portAdminStatus.description: The current administrative state of the port.

portOperStatus.name: portOperStatus
portOperStatus.description: The current operational state of the port.

portModemStatus.name: portModemStatus
portModemStatus.description: idle : system does not try to establish modem link. trying : system is trying to establish modem link. established : modem link has been established. If trying is written, modem will be reset and the system will try to re-establish modem link. If idle is set, system will not manage modem connection. When established is written, it will be ignored silently.

portLineQuality.name: portLineQuality
portLineQuality.description: The ascii string which describes the quality of link. Description can be distinct for DSL link type.

portUpStreamSpeed.name: portUpStreamSpeed
portUpStreamSpeed.description: An estimate of the port's current bandwidth in bits per second. For interfaces which do not vary in bandwidth or for those where no accurate estimation can be made, this object should contain the nominal bandwidth. If the bandwidth of the interface is greater than the maximum value reportable by this object then this object should report its maximum value (4,294,967,295). For a sub-layer which has no concept of bandwidth, this object should be zero.

portDownStreamSpeed.name: portDownStreamSpeed
portDownStreamSpeed.description: An estimate of the port's current bandwidth in bits per second. For interfaces which do not vary in bandwidth or for those where no accurate estimation can be made, this object should contain the nominal bandwidth. If the bandwidth of the interface is greater than the maximum value reportable by this object then this object should report its maximum value (4,294,967,295). For a sub-layer which has no concept of bandwidth, this object should be zero.

portLastModemStatusChange.name: portLastModemStatusChange
portLastModemStatusChange.description: Elasped time since modem status has been changed.

portSpecific.name: portSpecific
portSpecific.description: A reference to MIB definitions specific to the particular media being used to realize the module. It is recommended that this value point to an instance of a MIB object in the media-specific MIB, i.e., that this object have the semantics associated with the InstancePointer textual convention defined in RFC 1903. In fact, it is recommended that the module- specific MIB specify what value moduleSpecific should/can take for values of moduleType. If no MIB definitions specific to the particular media are available, the value should be set to the OBJECT IDENTIFIER { 0 0 }.

macNumber.name: macNumber
macNumber.description: The number of DSL modules (regardless of their current state) present on this system.

macTable.name: macTable
macTable.description: A list of module entries. The number of entries is given by the value of moduleNumber.

macEntry.name: macEntry
macEntry.description: Each entry contains one MAC address and its aging time.

macAddress.name: macAddress
macAddress.description: MAC address learned on this port.

agingTime.name: agingTime
agingTime.description: Elapased time since last RX activity from this MAC-addressed host.

dsVdslPMLos.name: dsVdslPMLos
dsVdslPMLos.description: The LOS total statistic value. set to 0 to clear count.

dsVdslPMClear.name: dsVdslPMClear
dsVdslPMClear.description: clear all error statistic counter with timer.

dsVdslPM15minInterval.name: dsVdslPM15minInterval
dsVdslPM15minInterval.description: Performance Data Interval number 1 is the most recent previous interval; interval 0 is current.

dsVdslPM1dayInterval.name: dsVdslPM1dayInterval
dsVdslPM1dayInterval.description: Performance Data Interval number 1 is the most recent previous interval; interval 0 is current.

dsVdslLineCfgProfileTable.name: dsVdslLineCfgProfileTable
dsVdslLineCfgProfileTable.description: This table contains information on the VDSL line configuration. One entry in this table reflects a profile defined by a manager which can be used to configure the VDSL line. Entries in this table MUST be maintained in a persistent manner.

dsVdslLineCfgProfileEntry.name: dsVdslLineCfgProfileEntry
dsVdslLineCfgProfileEntry.description: Each entry consists of a list of parameters that represents the configuration of a VDSL line. A default profile with an index of 'DEFVAL', will always exist and its parameters will be set to vendor specific values, unless otherwise specified in this document.

dsVdslLineCfgProfileName.name: dsVdslLineCfgProfileName
dsVdslLineCfgProfileName.description: This object identifies a row in this table. A default profile with an index of 'DEFVAL', will always exist and its parameters will be set to vendor specific values, unless otherwise specified in this document.

dsVdslLineCfgDownMaxSnrMgn.name: dsVdslLineCfgDownMaxSnrMgn
dsVdslLineCfgDownMaxSnrMgn.description: Specifies the maximum downstream Signal/Noise Margin in units of 0.25 dB, for a range of 0 to 31.75 dB.

dsVdslLineCfgDownMinSnrMgn.name: dsVdslLineCfgDownMinSnrMgn
dsVdslLineCfgDownMinSnrMgn.description: Specifies the minimum downstream Signal/Noise Margin in units of 0.25 dB, for a range of 0 to 31.75 dB.

dsVdslLineCfgDownTargetSnrMgn.name: dsVdslLineCfgDownTargetSnrMgn
dsVdslLineCfgDownTargetSnrMgn.description: Specifies the target downstream Signal/Noise Margin in units of 0.25 dB, for a range of 0 to 31.75 dB. This is the Noise Margin the transceivers must achieve with a BER of 10^-7 or better to successfully complete initialization.

dsVdslLineCfgUpMaxSnrMgn.name: dsVdslLineCfgUpMaxSnrMgn
dsVdslLineCfgUpMaxSnrMgn.description: Specifies the maximum upstream Signal/Noise Margin in units of 0.25 dB, for a range of 0 to 31.75 dB.

dsVdslLineCfgUpMinSnrMgn.name: dsVdslLineCfgUpMinSnrMgn
dsVdslLineCfgUpMinSnrMgn.description: Specifies the minimum upstream Signal/Noise Margin in units of 0.25 dB, for a range of 0 to 31.75 dB.

dsVdslLineCfgUpTargetSnrMgn.name: dsVdslLineCfgUpTargetSnrMgn
dsVdslLineCfgUpTargetSnrMgn.description: Specifies the target upstream Signal/Noise Margin in units of 0.25 dB, for a range of 0 to 31.75 dB. This is the Noise Margin the transceivers must achieve with a BER of 10^-7 or better to successfully complete initialization.

dsVdslLineCfgDownMaxDataRate.name: dsVdslLineCfgDownMaxDataRate
dsVdslLineCfgDownMaxDataRate.description: Specifies the maximum downstream slow channel data rate in steps of 1000 bits/second. The maximum aggregate downstream transmit speed of the line can be derived from the sum of maximum downstream fast and slow channel data rates.

dsVdslLineCfgDownMinDataRate.name: dsVdslLineCfgDownMinDataRate
dsVdslLineCfgDownMinDataRate.description: Specifies the minimum downstream slow channel data rate in steps of 1000 bits/second. The minimum aggregate downstream transmit speed of the line can be derived from the sum of minimum downstream fast and slow channel data rates.

dsVdslLineCfgUpMaxDataRate.name: dsVdslLineCfgUpMaxDataRate
dsVdslLineCfgUpMaxDataRate.description: Specifies the maximum upstream slow channel data rate in steps of 1000 bits/second.

dsVdslLineCfgUpMinDataRate.name: dsVdslLineCfgUpMinDataRate
dsVdslLineCfgUpMinDataRate.description: Specifies the minimum upstream slow channel data rate in steps of 1000 bits/second.

dsVdslLineCfgDownMaxInterDelay.name: dsVdslLineCfgDownMaxInterDelay
dsVdslLineCfgDownMaxInterDelay.description: Specifies the maximum interleave delay for the downstream slow channel.

dsVdslLineCfgUpMaxInterDelay.name: dsVdslLineCfgUpMaxInterDelay
dsVdslLineCfgUpMaxInterDelay.description: Specifies the maximum interleave delay for the upstream slow channel.

dsVdslLineCfgOptionband.description: dsVdsl Optional band ID. Annex B 6-64 (1) Annex A 6-32 (2) Annex B 32-64 (3) Exclude Option Band (4) Annex M

dsVdslLineCfgProfileAction.name: dsVdslLineCfgProfileAction
dsVdslLineCfgProfileAction.description: real set to profile parameter at the time. profile parameter is followings. dsVdslLineCfgStandard, dsVdslLineCfgLineProfile, dsVdslLineCfgToneDisableMode, dsVdslLineCfgOptionband.

dsVdslLineCfgProfRowStatus.name: dsVdslLineCfgProfRowStatus
dsVdslLineCfgProfRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or delete an existing row in this table. A profile activated by setting this object to 'active'. When 'active' is set, the system will validate the profile. Before a profile can be deleted or taken out of service, (by setting this object to 'destroy' or 'outOfService') it must be first unreferenced from all associated lines.
